  "prompt": "What equipment does a Korean BBQ restaurant kitchen need?",
  "response": "A Korean BBQ restaurant kitchen requires specialized equipment to ensure efficient and authentic preparation of dishes. Here\u2019s a list of essential equipment:\n\n### **Cooking Equipment**\n1. **Tabletop Grills**:  \n   - **Gas or Charcoal Grills**: Central to the dining experience, these grills are built into tables for on-table cooking. They can be gas-powered (for cleanliness and convenience) or charcoal-based (for flavor).\n   - **Non-Stick Grill Plates**: Replaceable or removable grill plates for easy cleaning.\n   - **Ventilation System**: Built-in exhaust hoods or ductless systems to manage smoke and odors.\n\n2. **Stovetops/Ranges**:  \n   - For cooking soups, stews, and side dishes in the kitchen.\n\n3. **Broilers/Grillers**:  \n   - For preparing meats and seafood in bulk.\n\n4. **Fryers**:  \n   - For making fried dishes like Korean fried chicken or tempura.\n\n---\n\n### **Preparation Equipment**\n1. **Meat Slicers**:  \n   - To thinly slice cuts of beef, pork, and other meats for BBQ.\n\n2. **Mixers/Blenders**:  \n   - For making marinades, sauces, and pastes.\n\n3. **Food Processors**:  \n   - For chopping and preparing vegetables and other ingredients.\n\n4. **Cutting Boards and Knives**:  \n   - A variety of sizes for meat and vegetable prep.\n\n---\n\n### **Storage Equipment**\n1. **Refrigerators and Freezers**:  \n   - For storing fresh meats, vegetables, and prepared ingredients.\n\n2. **Marinating Containers**:  \n   - Large containers for marinating meats in bulk.\n\n3. **Dry Storage Shelving**:  \n   - For spices, sauces, and non-perishable items.\n\n---\n\n### **Serving Equipment**\n1. **Banchan Containers**:  \n   - Small dishes for serving side dishes (banchan).\n\n2. **BBQ Tools**:  \n   - Tongs, scrapers, and spatulas for grilling.\n\n---\n\n### **Cleaning Equipment**\n1. **Dishwashers**:  \n   - For efficient cleaning of utensils and dishes.\n\n2. **Sink Stations**:  \n   - For handwashing and food prep cleaning.\n\n3. **Grease Traps**:  \n   - To manage grease from grilling.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Equipment**\n1. **Rice Cookers**:  \n   - For preparing large quantities of rice.\n\n2. **Steamers**:  \n   - For cooking vegetables, dumplings, or rice cakes.\n\n3. **Warming Lights/Heating Lamps**:  \n   - To keep prepared dishes warm before serving.\n\n4. **Beverage Station**:  \n   - For preparing and serving drinks like soju or Korean teas.\n\n---\n\n### **Dining Area Considerations**\n- **Exhaust Systems**: Strong ventilation to remove smoke and odors from the dining area.\n- **Table Setup**: Grill-embedded tables with comfortable seating.\n- **Disposable or Reusable Grill Covers**: For hygiene and ease of cleaning.\n\nBy investing in the right equipment, a Korean BBQ restaurant can ensure a seamless and enjoyable dining experience for customers.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
